    {
      "id": "1013266711877607",
      "score": 4,
      "review_title": "Has potential",
      "review_description": "While I was playing, it had a few good moments and some bad. First off, when I would throw the food into the air and hit it, it wouldn't actually cut and sometimes disappear through the ground. Another thing, when I use the knife it would barely swing, what I mean is it's slightly delayed, I mean it could just be a me problem, however it still has the same issue as before, where it just won't cut. I also saw so many other reviews saying grabbing the plate is just annoying, and I can agree. I say this because when I cut the food it spreads everywhere and sometimes even on the plate not clicking to its spot making it hard to grab. Other than those main issues, buying and getting more food from playing is actually fun and easy to do. It's not expensive or time wasting its easy and doing maybe 2 orders makes it a fun way to test new items that have been unlocked but when grabbing the food off the shelf my character moves back away from it making it hard to actually reach, so maybe add a auto grab or even lift the item when hovering to make it easier to reach. Overall a fun game, please keep updating and maybe even add side missions to keep engaged!",
      "date": 1775070306,
